hakari
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:the feast after a ceremonial funeral or other important occasion; a feast, f. Maori: Williams: [Maori h&amacr.kari]
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: [Ma. <b>hakari</b> feast] cf. P.M. Ryan Dict. Modern Maori (1995) 42.
